==English==

===Etymology===
From the French ''brunette'', "brown."  {{F}}

===Noun===
'''brunette'''
#''(US):'' A woman or girl with black or very dark-brown hair.
#''(elsewhere):'' A white woman or girl with dark-brown or black hair, often with dark eyes and a relatively dark or olive complexion.

